14 November 2019 The South African Government has noted the ruling of the Gauteng High Court of South Africa (Gauteng Division, Pretoria) regarding the protesters gathered at the UNHCR regional offices in Pretoria. The protesters are prohibited from contravening the by-laws of the City of Tshwane and the laws of South Africa. The government urges the protesters to abide by the decision of the High Court. South Africa is a constitutional democracy and a signatory to international instruments, which form part of Public International Law, and theseÂ  international instruments have been incorporated into our domestic law by the Refugees Act. South Africa has the legal instruments for refugees to exercise their rights, secure protection, and successfully integrate into South African communities. Enquiries: Phumla Williams - 083 501 0139 Issued by Government Communication and Information System (GCIS)